summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingEstée Lauder's multi-use, skin perfecting Double Wear Stay-in-Place 24-Hour Concealer conceals, contours, and highlights. It delivers 24-hour wear and oil control with immediate moisture.
details: DetailsBenefits24H weightless wear24H oil control24-hour non-caking24-hour non-streaking24-hour non-poring24-hour settle & crease-resistantImmediate moistureWater-resistantSweat, transfer & humidity-resistantMulti-use skin perfecting 24-hour concealerBlurs imperfections for a soft-focus matte finishHigh performance, featherweight formula melts onto skinFlexible, weightless, breathable wearMedium to full coverage concealer3D Sculpting Wand expertly designed for targeted, multi-use application so you can define & own your look with precision and controlThin, micro precision edge allows for precise, micro-controlled applicationMacro curved side forms to facial contours for all-over coverageMicro point tip is perfect for small & hard to reach areasKey IngredientsInvisiFlex technology: Flexible polymers move with facial expressions throughout the day for weightless, comfortable wearMicro silica spheres: Hollow silica spheres absorb sebum to provide powerful oil controlResearch Results97% said it blurs the look of imperfections immediately*95% said it blurs the look of pores immediately**90% said it left skin feeling moisturized immediately****Consumer testing on 114 panelists after using product for 1 week.**Consumer testing on 134 panelists after using product for 1 week.***Consumer testing on 136 panelists after using product for 1 week.Item 2635341How To UseThis 24-hour concealer with its 3D Sculpting Wand makes it easy to conceal, highlight, and contour for a multi-dimensional look.To start, choose a concealer shade based on your desired effect (always in your undertone).To Conceal:Use the same intensity as your exact-match foundation.Apply with the macro curved side of the brush to any areas that need coverage. Gently tap and smooth with ring finger, blending well.To Contour:Go 1-2 shades deeper than your foundation.To add dimension to your look, first use the macro curved side of the brush to swipe along the top of the forehead (near the hairline) and in the hollow under your natural cheekbone. Blend in.Then use the micro precision edge to stripe down the sides of your nose, and blend in.To Highlight:Go 1-2 shades lighter than your foundation.To lift and brighten your features, start with eyes. Use the macro curved side of the brush to apply 1-2 dots under eyes, then blend. Use the micro tip to draw a line from outer corner to temple, and blend in.Finish by using the micro precision edge to apply a thin line down the bridge of the nose, and blend in.More Concealer Tips:For best results, Estee recommends applying your full-coverage concealer after applying foundation.You can blend in with your fingertip, a beauty sponge or a fluffy brush--see what works best for you when creating different effects.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Methyl Trimethicone, Dimethicone, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Lauryl Peg-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Phenyl Trimethicone, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Polysilicone-11, Silica, Butylene Glycol, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Ppg-12/Smdi Copolymer, Tocopherol, Sodium Hyaluronate, Caffeine, Glycerin, Ethylhexylglycerin, Trihydroxystearin, Caprylyl Glycol, Triethyl Citrate, Alumina, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Barium Sulfate, Saccharide Isomerate, Laureth-12, Lecithin, Laureth-7, Hexylene Glycol, Citric Acid, Sodium Hydroxide, Sodium Carbonate, Dimethicone/Peg-10/15 Crosspolymer, Sodium Chloride, Xanthan Gum, Dipropylene Glycol, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Tocopheryl Acetate, Disodium Edta, Sodium Citrate, Phenoxyethanol, Potassium Sorbate, Sodium Dehydroacetate. May Contain (+/-): Mica, Titanium Dioxide (Ci 77891), Iron Oxides (Ci 77491), Iron Oxides (Ci 77492), Iron Oxides (Ci 77499).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Beautiful
reviews.comments: I love this, I use it as touchup concealer, it looks very natural and lasts all day. Buildable, a little fows a long way! PLEASE MAKE 1.5 COLOR SHADES!

reviews.headline: the best concealer
reviews.comments: it's the best

reviews.headline: Estee Lauder just solved my long- time concealer problem
reviews.comments: This concealer is beyond words.  I am literally shocked!  I have tried them ALL:  Drug store, Haus Labs, Natasha Denona you name it, I've tried it and it failed.  Jen Phelps on YT recommended this concealer...I sighed deeply and ordered it.  To my shock, it is beautiful.  the shade match was great (2.5 C), it goes on beautifully and it blends out really well.  It self-sets and it does dry down kind of quickly, but I don't mind doing one eye at a time. I do not need to powder (thank you Lord) under my eyes and after hours of wear this looks GREAT.  I will say that you do need to moisturize well, especially if you have dry, mature skin (like I do).  It covers my dark circles with a small amount of product...it's all that I have wanted in a concealer for a long time now.  THANK YOU ESTEE LAUDER ♡

reviews.headline: the updated 2025 version is not it
reviews.comments: This version (2025)  in the square tube is THICK and dries quickly making it a challenge to blend without being patchy or appear cakey. The version in the round tube (prior to 2025) is thinner but that didn't affect or impact the coverage. The coverage was incredible along with the blendability. This version (2025), the shades are LIGHTER than their previous versions. It's as if they mixed a white/gray mixer in every shade. I use Deep Amber 7N1 as my foundation ao that should tell you how deep my skin tone is. I used 6N in the old version and that is DEEPER than the 6.5 in this new version. That's crazy. The next color down, 7, is a whole step darker that it's no longer an undereye concealer.

reviews.headline: Estée Lauder concealer
reviews.comments: I live this.  Smooth application.

reviews.headline: Best Concealer I Have Used
reviews.comments: I heard many positive reviews about the Doublewear Concealer. I love it! The coverage is great and it works well on my mature skin. It dries so nicely - no creasing, shine or need to powder. I liked it so much, I went back to the store to buy an extra one for my purse. Very pleased!

reviews.headline: New go-to concealer
reviews.comments: This is a really great concealer. It has the coverage I need while still being very thin. It has a matte finish, but not drying. As long as you have some kind of moisturizer it'll be fine. Minimal creasing and no need to set it with powder. The Haus Labs concealer used to be my holy grail, but there wasn't enough coverage with that one so this has taken over as my top concealer now.

reviews.headline: Loveeeee
reviews.comments: Best concealer ever!

reviews.headline: I would buy this again!
reviews.comments: Did exactly as expected! Easy to use too!

reviews.headline: Not like the original formula
reviews.comments: Why change the formula if it was great?! Now this formula is cakey, matte & shades lighter thst the origional formula. Its so unnatural, dry & cakey under my eyes, making me look like I'm either older or makes me look like I dont know how to apply make up. It's absolutely awful. I've used the origional formula (round tub) for years & years- now I am going to have to find a new brand (not only my concealer but foundation as well). Very disappointing.

reviews.headline: I like it
reviews.comments: I got the wrong shade first off, but thats completely my fault. This reminds me so much of the Double Wear foundation;  coverage is phenomenal, little goes a long way AND I think it is self-setting… or just needs the tiniest bit of powder. Im still playing with it but i do like it, still doesnt beat my favorite though… yet, maybe.

reviews.headline: Too drying
reviews.comments: Good, medium coverage with one layer. Dries and sets very quickly though so you have to move fast. Ultimately I returned this because no matter how I prepped or set, this looked flaky and patchy, especially under the eyes. I can see how this would be good for weddings or in photos because from a distance it looks great. Up close is a different story.

reviews.headline: Question...
reviews.comments: Does anyone else have trouble getting actual product on the applicator? Every time I pull the applicator out there's barely any product on it...

reviews.headline: Way to dry
reviews.comments: I gave this concealer a few trys and even changed colors a few times.  It was just too dry under my eyes area and made my eyes look so old. Also the shades seemed to pull grey or white and did not look flattering under the eye.

reviews.headline: This concealer really changed my life!
reviews.comments: I never knew how to use concealer right and it must be because I didn't have the right product! This concealer amazed me from the very beginning! Pedro sold me on some amazing products and im so thankful he did! Brightens the face and really conceals! I LOVE IT!

reviews.headline: Good stuff
reviews.comments: I love how it doesn't cake, it bleads like butter

media.headline: Double Wear stay in place concealer

faceoff_positive.comments: The Estée Lauder Double Wear Stay-in-Place 24-Hour Concealer is a must-have for anyone seeking long-lasting, flawless coverage. Here's why I absolutely love it: • All-Day Wear: True to its name, this concealer stays put for up to 24 hours. It doesn't budge, crease, or fade—even through long days, heat, or humidity. Perfect for those with busy schedules or special events. • Lightweight Yet Full Coverage: The texture is lightweight and blendable, but it provides amazing full coverage. It effectively conceals dark circles, blemishes, and redness without feeling heavy or cakey. • Natural Finish: The finish is smooth and natural—neither too matte nor overly dewy. It creates a perfected, airbrushed look that works beautifully for everyday use or glam looks. • Versatile Formula: It works well for all skin types. Whether you have oily, dry, or combination skin, this concealer adapts without emphasizing texture or dry patches. • Shade Range: Estée Lauder offers a wide range of shades, making it easier to find a perfect match for your skin tone. • Effortless Application: The applicator is precise, making it easy to target specific areas like under the eyes or blemishes. It also blends seamlessly with a sponge, brush, or even fingertips. Pro Tip: For a flawless finish, pair it with the Estée Lauder Double Wear foundation or set it with a light powder for extra longevity. Final Thoughts: This concealer is a powerhouse! It's long-wearing, comfortable, and delivers consistent, flawless results. If you're looking for a reliable concealer that can handle anything your day throws at you, the Double Wear Stay-in-Place Concealer is worth every penny. Highly recommended for anyone who values performance and quality!
faceoff_positive.headline: Flawless coverage

faceoff_negative.comments:
Estee Lauder Double Wear concealer and foundation have been my go-to products for several years, but if the original concealer (in the round tube) is no longer available,  I will have to change brands because, unfortunately, I have never used a concealer that dries, thickens, and (worst of all) cakes as badly as the (relatively new?) formula of the Double Wear Stay in Place concealer. Since I like to keep a tube "in reserve" rather than risk running out, I ordered this concealer in late March, not realizing it was a different "formula" than the one I've used for years,  but I tried it just two days ago; so I am beyond the 30-day return timeframe and
 no refund is available according to Customer Care. Honestly, that doesn't bother me as much as the fact that it seems as though I can no longer get my favorite concealer.
faceoff_negative.headline: Cakes more than it conceals
